The glomerular filtration barrier is a complex biological sieve
nlike other capillaries, glomerular capillaries have a high permeability to water (hydraulic conductivity) yet, like other capillaries, are relatively impermeable to macromolecules. hese fundamental permeability properties depend on the unique, three-layer structure of the : the endothelium with its glycocalyx, the glomerular basement membrane () and podocytes (glomerular epithelial cells; ig. 2) [31].
