Conclusions
n summary, the various avenues of study of diabetic microalbuminuria reviewed converge on the glomerular endothelium. ur analysis therefore leads to the conclusion that this is the site of the initial damage that leads to the development of microalbuminuria in diabetes. he most important aspect of this damage is disruption of the endothelial glycocalyx through actions of mediators dysregulated by the diabetic milieu. ey players include ,  and proinflammatory cytokines (ig. 4). isturbance of endothelial cellβ€“podocyte communication contributes to and amplifies the endothelial lesion. rogression of microalbuminuria to overt nephropathy is accompanied by predictable structural changes in the glomerulus, including podocyte damage and loss. his is the result of the ongoing diabetic milieu and disturbed cellβ€“cell communication, but is also secondary to increased penetration of the  by serum proteins [97].
